set default deny

interface mgmt = "ens3"
interface wan = "wan0"
interface corp = "corp0"
interface iot = "iot0"
interface guest = "guest0"

table <corp_clients> { 10.10.0.0/24 }
table <iot_devices> { 10.80.0.0/24 }
table <guest_clients> { 10.81.0.0/24 }
table <dns_resolvers> { 10.10.0.53, 1.1.1.1, 9.9.9.9 }
table <blocked_iot> { 10.80.0.66, 10.80.0.67 }

queue standard on wan bandwidth 120mbit
queue guest_low on wan bandwidth 20mbit parent standard
queue iot_low on wan bandwidth 10mbit parent standard

pass in on mgmt proto tcp from any to any port 22 keep state
pass out on mgmt from any to any keep state

nat on wan from <corp_clients> to any -> wan
nat on wan from <iot_devices> to any -> wan
nat on wan from <guest_clients> to any -> wan

block in log (all) on iot from <blocked_iot> to any
block in log (user) on guest from <guest_clients> to <corp_clients>
block in log (user) on iot from <iot_devices> to <corp_clients>

pass in on corp proto udp from <corp_clients> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue standard
pass in on corp proto tcp from <corp_clients> to any port 443 keep state queue standard
pass in on corp proto tcp from <corp_clients> to any port 22 keep state queue standard

pass in on iot proto udp from <iot_devices> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue iot_low
pass in on iot proto tcp from <iot_devices> to any port 443 keep state queue iot_low

pass in on guest proto udp from <guest_clients> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue guest_low
pass in on guest proto tcp from <guest_clients> to any port 80 keep state queue guest_low
pass in on guest proto tcp from <guest_clients> to any port 443 keep state queue guest_low

block in log (all) on wan from any to any
block out log (user) on wan from any to any
